OL,3,CChris Hoy on redefining late-stage
OL,4,Ccancer: 'There's plenty of life left
OL,5,Cin us'
OL,7,FSix-time Olympic gold medallist Sir
OL,8,FChris Hoy is on a mission to redefine
OL,9,Fthe perception of people living with
OL,10,Fstage four cancer.
OL,12,FOn Friday morning in Glasgow, the
OL,13,Fcyclist said "there's plenty of life
OL,14,Fleft in us".
OL,16,FSir Chris revealed in 2024 that his
OL,17,Fprostate cancer had spread to his
OL,18,Fbones. Doctors subsequently gave him
OL,19,Fbetween two and four years to live.
OL,26,@uD@NOUvD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
